<subSubSection id="C37D650EFFF2FFACFF4CFF7C3FDBFF5D" pageId="2" pageNumber="232" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BD83685FFF2FFACFF4CFF7C3FDBFF5D" blockId="2.[151,1437,151,825]" pageId="2" pageNumber="232">
<emphasis id="B913EA97FFF2FFACFF4CFF7C3F0AFF15" bold="true" box="[199,334,151,177]" pageId="2" pageNumber="232">Etymology.</emphasis>
The species is named after Professor Cleide Costa, VSF’s MSc advisor and colleague of MAI, in recognition of her many contributions to the study of immature 
<taxonomicName id="4C674D06FFF2FFACFC48FF503A05FF71" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1758" box="[963,1089,187,213]" class="Insecta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="232" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="order">Coleoptera</taxonomicName>
, including fireflies and other bioluminescent beetles.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C37D650EFFF2FFACFF4CFEE93E8CFE2D" pageId="2" pageNumber="232" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BD83685FFF2FFACFF4CFEE93E8CFE2D" blockId="2.[151,1437,151,825]" pageId="2" pageNumber="232">
<emphasis id="B913EA97FFF2FFACFF4CFEE93F06FEB8" bold="true" box="[199,322,258,284]" pageId="2" pageNumber="232">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C674D06FFF2FFACFEC0FEE83C57FEB8" authorityName="Ferreira &amp; Keller &amp; Ivie" authorityYear="2022" box="[331,531,259,285]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Chespirito" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="232" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="costae">
<emphasis id="B913EA97FFF2FFACFEC0FEE83C57FEB8" box="[331,531,259,285]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="232">Chespirito costae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is morphologically similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C674D06FFF2FFACFCF8FEE83A7AFEB9" authorityName="Ferreira &amp; Keller &amp; Ivie" authorityYear="2022" box="[883,1086,259,285]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Chespirito" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="232" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="milleri">
<emphasis id="B913EA97FFF2FFACFCF8FEE83A7AFEB9" box="[883,1086,259,285]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="232">Chespirito milleri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
herein described, being easily separated from it by possessing the last tergite entire, apically round (
<figureCitation id="135C2A00FFF2FFACFC1EFECC3DAEFEE5" box="[917,1002,295,321]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[180,1407,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-20@3.[180,1407,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Dorsal habitus of Chespirito species.A) C. hintoni. B) C. costae. C). C. milleri. Ventral view of last three abdominal tergites (6–8). D) C. hintoni. E) C. costae. F). C. milleri. Dorsal view of last three abdominal ventrites. G) C. hintoni. H) C. costae. I). C. milleri. Scale bars: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6405134" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6405134/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="232">Fig. 1H</figureCitation>
) (vs. posteriorly notched in 
<taxonomicName id="4C674D06FFF2FFACFAA9FECC3BC8FEE5" authorityName="Ferreira &amp; Keller &amp; Ivie" authorityYear="2022" box="[1314,1420,295,321]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Chespirito" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="232" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="milleri">
<emphasis id="B913EA97FFF2FFACFAA9FECC3B71FEE5" box="[1314,1333,295,321]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="232">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B913EA97FFF2FFACFACAFECC3BC8FEE5" box="[1345,1420,295,321]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="232">milleri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), the elytra insertion entirely black (
<figureCitation id="135C2A00FFF2FFACFDABFEA03C33FEC1" box="[544,631,331,357]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[180,1407,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-20@3.[180,1407,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Dorsal habitus of Chespirito species.A) C. hintoni. B) C. costae. C). C. milleri. Ventral view of last three abdominal tergites (6–8). D) C. hintoni. E) C. costae. F). C. milleri. Dorsal view of last three abdominal ventrites. G) C. hintoni. H) C. costae. I). C. milleri. Scale bars: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6405134" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6405134/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="232">Fig. 1B</figureCitation>
) (vs. yellow in 
<taxonomicName id="4C674D06FFF2FFACFCA6FEA03DDEFEC1" authorityName="Ferreira &amp; Keller &amp; Ivie" authorityYear="2022" box="[813,922,331,357]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Chespirito" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="232" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="milleri">
<emphasis id="B913EA97FFF2FFACFCA6FEA03D04FEC1" box="[813,832,331,357]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="232">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B913EA97FFF2FFACFCC4FEA03DDEFEC1" box="[847,922,331,357]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="232">milleri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and by the shape of the male genitalia (
<figureCitation id="135C2A00FFF2FFACFAE4FEA03EFFFE2D" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,582,606]" captionTargetBox="[155,1432,192,549]" captionTargetId="figure-20@5.[148,1440,181,558]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Male genitalia, ventral and lateral view. A) C. hintoni. B) C. costae. C). C. milleri." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6405138" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6405138/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="232">Fig. 3B</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C37D650EFFF2FFACFF4CFE793B7AFCB1" pageId="2" pageNumber="232" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BD83685FFF2FFACFF4CFE793A0FFD55" blockId="2.[151,1437,151,825]" pageId="2" pageNumber="232">
<emphasis id="B913EA97FFF2FFACFF4CFE793F1DFE08" bold="true" box="[199,345,402,428]" pageId="2" pageNumber="232">Description.</emphasis>
General color dark brown (
<figureCitation id="135C2A00FFF2FFACFD04FE783CB4FE09" box="[655,752,403,429]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[180,1407,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-20@3.[180,1407,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Dorsal habitus of Chespirito species.A) C. hintoni. B) C. costae. C). C. milleri. Ventral view of last three abdominal tergites (6–8). D) C. hintoni. E) C. costae. F). C. milleri. Dorsal view of last three abdominal ventrites. G) C. hintoni. H) C. costae. I). C. milleri. Scale bars: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6405134" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6405134/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="232">Figs. 1B</figureCitation>
), mandibles and last three abdominal segments yellow (
<figureCitation id="135C2A00FFF2FFACFAEFFE783EADFE75" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[180,1407,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-20@3.[180,1407,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Dorsal habitus of Chespirito species.A) C. hintoni. B) C. costae. C). C. milleri. Ventral view of last three abdominal tergites (6–8). D) C. hintoni. E) C. costae. F). C. milleri. Dorsal view of last three abdominal ventrites. G) C. hintoni. H) C. costae. I). C. milleri. Scale bars: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6405134" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6405134/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="232">Figs. 1E, 1H</figureCitation>
). Head as long as wide, posterior 2/3 covered by pronotum (
<figureCitation id="135C2A00FFF2FFACFC1FFE5C3DAFFE75" box="[916,1003,439,465]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[180,1407,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-20@3.[180,1407,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Dorsal habitus of Chespirito species.A) C. hintoni. B) C. costae. C). C. milleri. Ventral view of last three abdominal tergites (6–8). D) C. hintoni. E) C. costae. F). C. milleri. Dorsal view of last three abdominal ventrites. G) C. hintoni. H) C. costae. I). C. milleri. Scale bars: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6405134" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6405134/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="232">Fig. 1B</figureCitation>
). Antennae when extended posteriorly reaching apical third of elytra (
<figureCitation id="135C2A00FFF2FFACFE65FE303C00FE51" box="[494,580,475,501]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[180,1407,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-20@3.[180,1407,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Dorsal habitus of Chespirito species.A) C. hintoni. B) C. costae. C). C. milleri. Ventral view of last three abdominal tergites (6–8). D) C. hintoni. E) C. costae. F). C. milleri. Dorsal view of last three abdominal ventrites. G) C. hintoni. H) C. costae. I). C. milleri. Scale bars: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6405134" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6405134/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="232">Fig. 1B</figureCitation>
). Pronotum not constricted medially; anterior angles round; posterior margin bisinuate (
<figureCitation id="135C2A00FFF2FFACFE84FE143F2DFDBD" box="[271,361,511,537]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[180,1407,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-20@3.[180,1407,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Dorsal habitus of Chespirito species.A) C. hintoni. B) C. costae. C). C. milleri. Ventral view of last three abdominal tergites (6–8). D) C. hintoni. E) C. costae. F). C. milleri. Dorsal view of last three abdominal ventrites. G) C. hintoni. H) C. costae. I). C. milleri. Scale bars: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6405134" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6405134/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="232">Fig. 1B</figureCitation>
); median longitudinal carina strongly visible throughout (
<figureCitation id="135C2A00FFF2FFACFB81FE143A21FDBD" box="[1034,1125,511,537]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[180,1407,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-20@3.[180,1407,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Dorsal habitus of Chespirito species.A) C. hintoni. B) C. costae. C). C. milleri. Ventral view of last three abdominal tergites (6–8). D) C. hintoni. E) C. costae. F). C. milleri. Dorsal view of last three abdominal ventrites. G) C. hintoni. H) C. costae. I). C. milleri. Scale bars: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6405134" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6405134/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="232">Fig. 1B</figureCitation>
). Elytra ca. 3.2× length of pronotum; weakly dehiscent; basally subparallel (
<figureCitation id="135C2A00FFF2FFACFD5AFDC83D6FFD99" box="[721,811,547,573]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[180,1407,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-20@3.[180,1407,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Dorsal habitus of Chespirito species.A) C. hintoni. B) C. costae. C). C. milleri. Ventral view of last three abdominal tergites (6–8). D) C. hintoni. E) C. costae. F). C. milleri. Dorsal view of last three abdominal ventrites. G) C. hintoni. H) C. costae. I). C. milleri. Scale bars: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6405134" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6405134/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="232">Fig. 1B</figureCitation>
); with two weakly developed elytral costae (
<figureCitation id="135C2A00FFF2FFACFABFFDC83BC9FD99" box="[1332,1421,547,573]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[180,1407,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-20@3.[180,1407,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Dorsal habitus of Chespirito species.A) C. hintoni. B) C. costae. C). C. milleri. Ventral view of last three abdominal tergites (6–8). D) C. hintoni. E) C. costae. F). C. milleri. Dorsal view of last three abdominal ventrites. G) C. hintoni. H) C. costae. I). C. milleri. Scale bars: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6405134" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6405134/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="232">Fig. 1B</figureCitation>
). Scutellar shield posteriorly round (
<figureCitation id="135C2A00FFF2FFACFD94FDAC3C33FDC5" box="[543,631,583,609]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[180,1407,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-20@3.[180,1407,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Dorsal habitus of Chespirito species.A) C. hintoni. B) C. costae. C). C. milleri. Ventral view of last three abdominal tergites (6–8). D) C. hintoni. E) C. costae. F). C. milleri. Dorsal view of last three abdominal ventrites. G) C. hintoni. H) C. costae. I). C. milleri. Scale bars: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6405134" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6405134/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="232">Fig. 1B</figureCitation>
). Abdomen with tergite VIII entire, apically round (
<figureCitation id="135C2A00FFF2FFACFB4AFDAC3B5FFDC5" box="[1217,1307,583,609]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[180,1407,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-20@3.[180,1407,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Dorsal habitus of Chespirito species.A) C. hintoni. B) C. costae. C). C. milleri. Ventral view of last three abdominal tergites (6–8). D) C. hintoni. E) C. costae. F). C. milleri. Dorsal view of last three abdominal ventrites. G) C. hintoni. H) C. costae. I). C. milleri. Scale bars: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6405134" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6405134/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="232">Fig. 1H</figureCitation>
); ventrite 7 with shallow notch posteriorly (
<figureCitation id="135C2A00FFF2FFACFE7CFD803C0FFD21" box="[503,587,619,645]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[180,1407,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-20@3.[180,1407,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Dorsal habitus of Chespirito species.A) C. hintoni. B) C. costae. C). C. milleri. Ventral view of last three abdominal tergites (6–8). D) C. hintoni. E) C. costae. F). C. milleri. Dorsal view of last three abdominal ventrites. G) C. hintoni. H) C. costae. I). C. milleri. Scale bars: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6405134" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6405134/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="232">Fig. 1E</figureCitation>
); ventrite 8 elongate, fusiform, longer than wide, entire, not notched apically (
<figureCitation id="135C2A00FFF2FFACFF2BFD643EBCFD0D" box="[160,248,655,681]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[180,1407,181,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-20@3.[180,1407,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Dorsal habitus of Chespirito species.A) C. hintoni. B) C. costae. C). C. milleri. Ventral view of last three abdominal tergites (6–8). D) C. hintoni. E) C. costae. F). C. milleri. Dorsal view of last three abdominal ventrites. G) C. hintoni. H) C. costae. I). C. milleri. Scale bars: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6405134" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6405134/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="232">Fig. 1E</figureCitation>
). Male genitalia with median lobe stout, fusiform, apically fan-shaped, round, in ventral view bearing paired strut-like structure, divergent apically (
<figureCitation id="135C2A00FFF2FFACFD18FD583CADFD69" box="[659,745,691,717]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,582,606]" captionTargetBox="[155,1432,192,549]" captionTargetId="figure-20@5.[148,1440,181,558]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Male genitalia, ventral and lateral view. A) C. hintoni. B) C. costae. C). C. milleri." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6405138" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6405138/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="232">Fig. 3B</figureCitation>
); parameres bulb-shaped, apically round (
<figureCitation id="135C2A00FFF2FFACFB30FD583B55FD69" box="[1211,1297,691,717]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,582,606]" captionTargetBox="[155,1432,192,549]" captionTargetId="figure-20@5.[148,1440,181,558]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Male genitalia, ventral and lateral view. A) C. hintoni. B) C. costae. C). C. milleri." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6405138" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6405138/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="232">Fig. 3B</figureCitation>
), 1/5 shorter than median lobe; phallobase small, longer than wide, posteriorly rounded (
<figureCitation id="135C2A00FFF2FFACFC6DFD3C3A7AFD55" box="[998,1086,727,753]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,582,606]" captionTargetBox="[155,1432,192,549]" captionTargetId="figure-20@5.[148,1440,181,558]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Male genitalia, ventral and lateral view. A) C. hintoni. B) C. costae. C). C. milleri." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6405138" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6405138/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="232">Fig. 3B</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD83685FFF2FFACFF4CFD103B7AFCB1" blockId="2.[151,1437,151,825]" box="[199,1342,762,789]" pageId="2" pageNumber="232">
